main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects in Chicago during June 1963.
interesting points: Reports included observations of 20 objects visible for 2 minutes on June 14, 1963, A round silver object was spotted flying North to South and disappearing over a lake on June 23, 1963, Weather conditions were described as clear and cold on the nights of the observations, Some reports referenced possible misidentification as birds or other atmospheric phenomena, Several eyewitness accounts indicate the objects moved silently and varied in size.
